Class Constant

  • java.lang.Object
    • Argument
      • Constant
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.Comparator, Symbol
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArgString

    public class Constant
extends Argument
implements Symbol
    If a symbol, string, or boolean value appears as an argument in a literal, it is a Constant. The UserDefinedProperty feature may employ constants. The Parser can parse them.
